    "asOf": "2023-06-07",
    "date": "2024-06-24T19:38:27Z",
    "text": "Improving Mental Health and Drug Treatment Act of 2023\u00a0\n\nThis bill permanently allows state Medicaid programs to receive federal payment for substance-use disorder services that are provided at institutions for mental diseases (IMDs) for individuals aged 21 to 64. The bill also extends the maximum length of stay over a 12-month period from 30 days to 45 days and requires state Medicaid programs to review IMD compliance with relevant standards of care."
